description: Mounded clumps on forest soil, bright green from recent rains. Sporangia purple-brown, capsule curved, about 1/4 were releasing spores. Plants to 2-3 cm tall. Leaf midrib with 4-6 lamella, each 4-5 cells tall. Alar cells at leaf base thickened, but not especially differentiated from the rest of the leaf.
Uncommon, irregular tufts on rotten wood just above high water line. No sporophytes found. Habitat shrubby, and flooded with 1-4 cm of water all summer long, though currently damp-dry in mid-winter.
